      <p><font size="-1"><br>
      <font size="+1"><a name="path4"></a><font face="ZapfHumnst Dm BT" color="#800000"><b>Selected Academic Publications</b></font></font><font size="-5">&nbsp;</font></font>
		  
		  <p><font size="-1">
			  <p><font face="ZapfHumnst Dm BT"><font color="#800000"><b><a name="66"></a>--Alfred Russel Wallace Notes: </b></font></font><font face="ZapfHumnst Dm BT"><font color="#800000"><em>Alfred Russel Wallace Notes</em> is a peer-reviewed and irregularly published note series edited by Charles H. Smith. Its subjects are elements of the life and thought of British naturalist and social critic Alfred Russel Wallace (1823-1913), co-discoverer of the principle of natural selection.</font></font></font>
			  
