      <font size="-1"><p><font size="-1">
        <font size="-1"><a name="path7"></a><b><font color="#800000" size="+1" face="ZapfHumnst Dm BT">Most 
        Unusual Achievement</font></b>&nbsp; </font> </font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">On an otherwise
          ordinary  day in the spring of 1966, while pitching in a junior varsity
          high school  baseball game, I picked off two runners in a row who had
          reached first  base on consecutive at-bats. Neither was caught in the
          act of a steal  attempt, mind you--they just weren't able to beat the
          tag, returning to  first. And I am right-handed, not left-handed: considering
          that, this  must be nearly as rare a feat as taking part in an
          unassisted triple play (well, almost, anyway...)!</font> 
      <p><br>
        <font size="+1"><a name="path6"></a><b><font face="ZapfHumnst Dm BT" color="#800000">Web 
        Materials Created by Charles Smith</font></b></font> </font> 
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">I have written and/or 
        compiled and maintain the following materials, available on the World 
        Wide Web:</font>
   
      <p><b><i><font color="#800000" size="-1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font><font color="#800000">Alfred 
        Russel Wallace-Related Websites:</font></i></b>&nbsp; 
      <ul>
        <ul>
		          <li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"><u><a href="index1.htm"><i><font color="3333ff">The 
            Alfred Russel Wallace Page</font></i></a></u> (extensive materials 
            by and about the extraordinary English evolutionist, naturalist, and 
            social critic, who lived from 1823-1913)</font></li>
          <ul>
            <li><font size="-1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/wallace/chsarwp.htm"><i><font color="3333ff">Alfred 
              R. Wallace: Evolution of an Evolutionist</font></i></a> (monographic analysis)</font></li>
            <li><font size="-1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/wallace/wallcon.htm"><font color="3333ff">&quot;Wallace 
              on Conservation&quot;</font></a> (a collection of Wallace's conservation-related 
              writings)</font></li>
            <li><font size="-1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/wallace/writings.htm"><font color="3333ff">&quot;Full-Text
                     of Wallace's Published Writings&quot;</font></a> (some eleven hundred texts)</font></li>
            <li><font size="-1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/wallace/bibintro.htm"><font color="3333ff">&quot;Bibliography 
              of the Writings of Alfred Russel Wallace&quot;</font></a></font></li>
            <li><font size="-1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/wallace/names.htm"><font color="3333ff">&quot;Personal
                     Names Index to the Writings of Alfred Russel Wallace&quot;</font></a> 
              (close to 3000 names included in his more than 1100 publications)</font></li>
          </ul>
          <li><font size="-1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><i><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/once/welcome.htm"><font color="3333ff">The 
            Once and Future Wallace, or, Evolutionary Theorizing in the Manner 
            of Alfred Russel Wallace</font></a></i> (a website dwelling on my 
            revisionist views of Wallace's thought, including biogeographic and 
            systems theory modeling based on &quot;final causes&quot; thinking)</font></li>
          <li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"><a href="http://wallace-online.org/" target="_top"><font color="3333ff"><em>Wallace Online</em></font></a> (John van Wyhe, Charles H. Smith, et al.)</font></li>
          
        </ul>
      </ul>
      <p><b><i><font color="#800000" size="-1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font><font color="#800000">Natural 
        History and History-Related Databases:</font></i></b> 
      <ul>
        <ul>
          <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/biogeog/"><i><font color="3333ff">Early 
            Classics in Biogeography, Distribution, and Diversity Studies: To 
            1950</font></i></a> (an enhanced bibliography with links to: (1) the 
            full-text of many of the items listed, and (2) biographical information 
            on the authors)</font></li>
          <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"><i><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/biogeog/index2.htm"><font color="3333ff">Early 
            Classics in Biogeography, Distribution, and Diversity Studies: 1951-1975</font></a></i> 
            (a continuation of the previous service)</font></li>
          <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"><i><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/chronob/homelist.htm"><font color="3333ff">Some
                     Biogeographers, Evolutionists and Ecologists: Chrono-Biographical
                     Sketches</font></a></i> (a collection of more than 280
                     short biographical  sketches)</font></li>
          <li><font size="-1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><i><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/once/welcome.htm"><font color="3333ff">The 
            Once and Future Wallace, or, Evolutionary Theorizing in the Manner 
            of Alfred Russel Wallace</font></a></i> (a website dwelling on my 
            revisionist views of Wallace's thought, including biogeographic and 
            systems theory modeling based on &quot;final causes&quot; thinking)</font></li>
          <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"><i><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/australia/"><font color="3333ff">Nineteenth 
            Century Exploration of Australia</font></a></i> (a website focusing 
            on the routes of the Inland explorers)</font></li>
          <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">link to <a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/DISS/dissertation.htm"><font color="3333ff">Ph.D.
                Dissertation</font></a> (<em>The
            Dynamics of Animal Distribution: An Evolutionary/Ecological Model</em>)</font></li>
          <li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"><u><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/mamm/HERPFAUN.htm"><i><font color="3333ff">HERPFAUN</font></i></a></u> 
            (a taxon- and faunal unit-referenced bibliography of publications
                 concerning the geographical distribution of reptiles and amphibians)</font> </li>
          <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/mamm/MAMMFAUN.htm"><i><font color="3333ff">MAMMFAUN</font></i></a> 
            (a taxon- and faunal unit-referenced bibliography of publications 
            concerning the geographical distribution of mammals)</font></li>
          <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/faunmaps/index.htm"><font color="3333ff"><i>The Distribution
              of Mammals: Mammal Families Distribution Maps</i></font></a> (family-level range
              maps)</font></li>
        </ul>
      </ul>
      <b><i><font color="#800000" size="-1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font><font color="#800000">Music-Related 
      Materials:</font></i></b>&nbsp; 
      <ul>
        <ul>
          <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"><i><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/MALVINA/homep.htm"><font color="3333ff">Malvina 
            Reynolds: Song Lyrics and Poems</font></a></i> (poetry and song lyrics 
            from the celebrated 1950s-70s topical and children's songs composer)</font></li>
          <li> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"><u><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/music"><i><font color="3333ff">The 
            Classical Music Navigator</font></i></a></u> (a web-based service 
            facilitating the identification and linking of composers and their 
            works, styles, and influences)</font></li>
          <li><font size="-1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/essays/FOLK111.htm"><i><font color="3333ff">The
                     111 Greatest Acts of the Anglo-American Folk Music Tradition...</font></i></a> 
            (an ordered list of 111+ folkies and folk-rockers, with links to
            websites)</font> </li>
          <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AH5QJFSPBTBHPKN2W4FJ62VIUEJA?preview=true"><font color="3333ff">music 
            CD and book reviews for Amazon.com</font></a></font></li>
          <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/essays/youwere.htm"><font color="3333ff">&quot;We 
            Five's 'You Were on My Mind': Ode to a Sometimes-Maligned Song&quot;</font></a></font></li>
			          <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/essays/besttenhitsongs.htm"><font color="3333ff">&quot;The Best Ten Hit Message Songs of the 60s: A Reflection&quot;</font></a></font></li>
                      <li><font size="-1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/sci/cdlist.htm"><font color="3333ff">Suggestions 
            for a Contemporary Music Genres Collection</font></a> (classified 
            browse list)</font><font size="-4"><br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;</font> </li>
